Hello Families of American International Academy:

Below are the links to Re-Enroll your current student into the upcoming school year.

If you are enrolling for the first time, please select the New Student Enrollment Application.

Because we use Google Forms to safely collect our data, you will need to log into your Google account to access this form. If you do not have a Google/Gmail account, please take the few minutes to create one so that your data stays safe in the hands of the American International Academy Administrative staff.

Greetings American International Academy Families:

The Academy is working hard to prepare for the 20-21 School Year. Due to COVID-19, school will look different for the upcoming school year. AIA's priority is to provide a quality education in the safest environment possible for each of our students.

We are reaching out to families to provide feedback to us on your thoughts and concerns about returning to school in the Fall 2020. Please take a moment to click the link and complete a short survey about how you would like for your child(ren) to return to school in the fall.

Please submit the survey by Friday, July 31, 2020.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfgdTPe9SuvBdKeWwcpfIiHTbxCjn-G0IugffQ89yCT42r8ZA/viewform?usp=sf_link

If you have any questions, please contact the school at:

(734)713-5525.

Stay Safe, Stay Healthy, Keep Learning

AIA Staf

Good morning AIA Families:
We just want to remind families of AIA's exciting Summer Learning Backpack Program. Due to the COVID- 19, the district has decided to create a learning backpack for our students to practice skills that they need to maintain and practice for transition into the next school year.

This is not a traditional summer school program and students will have a backpack that they will use to engage in independent learning opportunities. We will have videos that will be made available about the materials in the Backpacks and you may contact the school if you have any questions.

AIA staff will begin delivering Summer Learning Backpacks to the homes of current AIA (K-5 ) students Tuesday, July 21st. Please be on the look out for an AIA bus in your neighborhood today.

Stay Safe, Stay Healthy, Keep Learning!

We miss you all

-AIA Staff--

Stay healthy and stay safe!

Greetings AIA Families:

It's getting close to that time of year! The last day of classes for American International Academy School District students is on Friday, June 12, 2020.

Students should continue to complete schoolwork online or in their homework packets.

All completed homework packets must be turned in to the office of your respective student(s) no later than Wednesday, June 10th so that they can be graded and report cards can be completed.

Update: As they become available, homework packets are being posted on the American International Academy website. Visit:

americanintlacademy.com

Click on "COVID-19 UPDATES" to reach available online homework packets.

Thank you for your continued patience and support!

---AIA Administration

Hello Families of American International Academy:

Below are the links to Re-Enroll your current student into the upcoming school year.

If you are enrolling for the first time, please select the New Student Enrollment Application.

Because we use Google Forms to safely collect our data, you will need to log into your Google account to access this form. If you do not have a Google/Gmail account, please take the few minutes to create one so that your data stays safe in the hands of just American International Academy Administrative staff.

**American International Academy uses Google Forms . This transmission of data uses SSL to encrypt all the data and complies with all HIPAA compliance laws.**

Here are the links to the sites:

Good Evening AIA Families,

The AIA Instructional Staff has been working hard to complete set up of the Google Classrooms, Khan Academy, and more online platforms and will be reaching out soon with additional information. In the meantime, you will find instructions on how to set up an account in Khan Academy for your student at home and will be followed with posts of daily learning sample schedules for each grade level to help ensure that student learning continues during this unprecedented time. If you have any questions, don't hesitate to reach out. Please stay safe.

--AIA Administration

LOVE IS SOMETHING YOU DO 🙌🏽

On this Labor Day, we are dedicating our time, energy, and talent laboring for the student and parent community of Inkster, getting American International Academy ready to welcome them back to their EXCEPTIONAL school of choice!

🎯 DAY 1 --> Tuesday, September 3rd.

💯 We are on a mission to positively impact the overall growth of the Inkster community as a whole...it is our paramount concern.

👨🏽‍🎓👩🏽‍🎓 The work that we are doing today will forever change the life of every student who walks thru our doors. We won't stop until we MAXIMIZE their potential and help them become the great leaders they were born to be.

#HappyLaborDay #ItsALaborOfLove #AIAHighSchool #AIAMiddleSchool #AIAElementarySchool #LoveLaughLearn

Thomas White Jeff Wilder

🍁Happy September! Hang tight...it's going to be a great month!!

August has been a really busy month for us here at American International Academy between upgrading ALL of our campuses giving them a fresh, NEW look, bringing more staff on board (we're growing by leaps & bounds), having a successful Back-to-School Bash, and making some big decisions that will positively impact every one of our students' future.

We're prepared for having an exceptional school year and we are EXCITED about seeing all of our students & meeting some of our new parents for the 1st Day of School Tuesday, Sept. 3rd 🤩

Here's to a spectacular September! #GoVikings #AIAHighSchoolCampus

Thomas White Jeff Wilder
